20
00:01:37,530 --> 00:01:43,610
The formal theory of this interaction is
quantum chromodynamics, also called QCD.

21
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:51,170
Color can take three different values,
red, blue, and green for quarks.

22
00:01:51,170 --> 00:01:54,630
We indicate it by a lower index when appropriate.

23
00:01:54,630 --> 00:02:00,680
A quark can carry only one non zero color,
antiquarks carry one anti-color.

24
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:05,818
The interaction between quarks proceeds
through the exchange of color.

25
00:02:05,818 --> 00:02:12,510
The intermediate vector bosons transmitting
the strong force are the eight gluons, g.

26
00:02:12,510 --> 00:02:17,960
They carry a color and an anti-color,
and therefore are not color neutral.

27
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:23,140
This is in contrast to the photon which couples
to the electromagnetic charge but

28
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:25,120
does not carry one itself.

29
00:02:26,310 --> 00:02:30,440
For strong interaction,
there are eight gluons in total.

30
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,870
With three colors and

31
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:36,335
three anti-colors one would expect
a total of nine combinations.

32
00:02:36,335 --> 00:02:40,577
One of them, the fully symmetric combination,
that is

33
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:45,479
red-antired plus green-antigreen plus 
blue-antiblue,

34
00:02:45,479 --> 00:02:50,490
has no net color, it does not
participate in strong interaction and

35
00:02:50,490 --> 00:02:52,670
